				\begin{document}$${\text{RT}}\, - \,{\text{PCR}}\,{\text{ inhibition}}\, = \, \, (1 - 10^{{\Delta{\text{Cq}}/{\text{m}}}} )\, \times \,100\%$$\end{document}RT-PCRinhibition=(1-10ΔCq/m)×100%where ΔCq = Cq value (sample RNA + EC RNA) − Cq value (water RNA + EC RNA) and m = slope of the standard curve. The acceptable level of RT-PCR inhibition was ≤ 75% according to the value recommended in the ISO standard procedure for quantitative detection of norovirus in food and water (ISO, 2017).
